Any time I mention thyroid supplementation I should add a disclaimer that before taking anything you should:

1. Read Dr. Broda Barnes' hypothyroidism book
2. Read Danny Roddy's demystifying thyroid supplementation article
3. Maybe lurk Ray Peat mom facebook groups for 2-3 months

T3 is not like supplements that you can pop an entire bottle of and just piss it out afterwards, it's a really potent and potentially dangerous hormone (and should always be started at the lowest possible dose of 1 mcg), it's very much worth it to invest some time reading first.

I know it's boring to see me mention these same books and articles for the 100th time but still some due diligence is always good and people are used to useless supps so their instinct is to just take an entire T3 pill on empty stomach without measuring pulse and see what happens
